                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.01/105</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-13T16:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 13, 1916, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A conference of representatives of governors of the seventeen loyal provinces is
                    called to meet Nanking May 15 by arrangement between Feng and the Government
                    leaders. The principal argument for consideration is the further continuance in
                    office of Yuan. Events in Shantung and the lack of funds emphasize the necessity
                    of definite understanding on the part of loyal provinces, either to give Yuan
                    Government united and sufficient support or to displace Yuan and thus invite
                    reunion with the South. In any event, personal power of Yuan is destroyed and he
                    would be retained only as formal head.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
